def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    if axis == 0:
        # No bug fix needed for grouping along the index
        pass
    else:
        group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)
        
        if key is None:
            # Grouping by column labels
            keys = group_axis

            groupings = [Grouping(group_axis, gpr, obj=obj, name=name, level=level, sort=sort, observed=observed) 
                         for gpr, name in zip(keys, keys.names)]
        else:
            # Grouping by specified keys
            keys = [key] if isinstance(key, str) else key
            
            groupings = [Grouping(group_axis, gpr, obj=obj, name=name, level=level, sort=sort, observed=observed) 
                         for gpr, name in zip(keys, keys)]

    # create the internals grouper
    grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, groupings, sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
    return grouper, [], obj
